# AI-Powered Tax Search & Analytics Platform

Smart tax-document search assistant for operations, compliance, and audit teams.

---

## Project Structure

```
/backend          Express API — all search logic
/frontend         React UI — search bar, filters, results grid
/test-harness     QA test script (SEMANTIC-001, FUZZY-001)
/data             Seed data (20 sample filings)
```

---

## Quick Start

### 1. Backend

```bash
cd backend
npm install
npm start
# API running at http://localhost:4000
```

### 2. Frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm start
# UI running at http://localhost:3000
```

### 3. QA Test Harness

> Make sure the backend is running first.

```bash
cd test-harness
npm install
npm test
# or with a custom URL:
node run-tests.js --base-url http://localhost:4000
```

---

## API Reference

### `GET /api/search`

Unified search endpoint supporting all modes.

| Parameter        | Type    | Description                                              |
|------------------|---------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| `query`          | string  | Search text                                              |
| `mode`           | string  | `basic` \| `semantic` \| `fuzzy` \| `wildcard` \| `boolean` |
| `targetField`    | string  | For fuzzy: `clientName` or `employerName`                |
| `missingSSN`     | boolean | Filter records with missing/empty SSN                    |
| `wagesGreaterThan` | number | Filter wages strictly above threshold                  |
| `wagesMin`       | number  | Wage band lower bound (inclusive)                        |
| `wagesMax`       | number  | Wage band upper bound (inclusive)                        |
| `state`          | string  | Two-letter state code (e.g., `CA`)                       |
| `taxYear`        | number  | Four-digit year (e.g., `2021`)                           |
| `employerName`   | string  | Employer name substring match                            |
| `formType`       | string  | `W-2` or `1099`                                          |
| `flags`          | string  | `missing_ssn`, `missing_employer`, `high_wage`           |
| `page`           | number  | Page number (default: 1)                                 |
| `pageSize`       | number  | Results per page (default: 50)                           |

**Example requests:**

```
# 1.1 Missing SSN
GET /api/search?missingSSN=true

# 1.2 High-income filings
GET /api/search?wagesGreaterThan=1000000

# 1.3 State + year
GET /api/search?state=CA&taxYear=2021

# 1.4 Employer + form + year
GET /api/search?employerName=Acme+Corp&formType=W-2&taxYear=2022

# 2.1 Semantic
GET /api/search?query=tech+companies&mode=semantic

# 3.1 Fuzzy client name
GET /api/search?query=Jhon+Smth&mode=fuzzy

# 3.2 Fuzzy employer
GET /api/search?query=Acmee+Corp&mode=fuzzy&targetField=employerName

# 4.1 Wildcard
GET /api/search?query=Sm*&mode=wildcard

# 5.1 Boolean
GET /api/search?query=Smith+OR+Johnson&mode=boolean&taxYear=2022

# 6.1 Wage band
GET /api/search?wagesMin=50000&wagesMax=100000
```

---

### `GET /api/facets`

Returns grouped counts by `formType`, `taxYear`, and `state`.

Accepts the same filter params as `/api/search` (no `query`/`mode`).

```
GET /api/facets
GET /api/facets?state=CA
```

---

### `GET /api/suggest`

Autocomplete / suggest-as-you-type.

| Parameter | Type   | Description                              |
|-----------|--------|------------------------------------------|
| `prefix`  | string | Partial text typed by the user           |
| `scope`   | string | `client` \| `employer` \| `all` (default) |

```
GET /api/suggest?prefix=Jan
GET /api/suggest?prefix=Tech&scope=employer
```

---

## UI Features

- **Single search bar** with autocomplete dropdown
- **Search mode selector**: Basic / Semantic / Fuzzy / Wildcard / Boolean
- **Compact filter row**: Year, Form, State, Flags (Missing SSN, Missing Employer, High Wage)
- **Facets panel**: Click any facet to drill down
- **Results grid**: Client, Employer, Form, Year, State, Wages, Flags — sortable columns
- **Pagination**: 10 results per page

---

## QA Test Cases

| ID           | Input                          | Expected                                              |
|--------------|--------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| SEMANTIC-001 | `"tech companies"`, semantic   | Results map to technology-related employers           |
| FUZZY-001    | `"Jhon Smth"`, fuzzy           | "John Smith" appears in top 3 results                 |
